%AUTOLIST :+
+  Use%AUTOLIST+to turn AUTOLIST mode on or off ("ON" is the default).
   If AUTOLIST mode is on, data is automatically formatted and written t
   ISPF file when it is saved. The list file is normally printed when yo
   from ISPF. If AUTOLIST mode is off, data is not written to the list f
   If you want to maintain hardcopy listings of the latest versions of y
   program source, you should set AUTOLIST on. Then the listings will be
   created automatically.

   More topic will be presented in the EDIT tutorial.
+
+Enter%&EPF+to exit the tutorial and return to the EDIT modes control pa
+Hit%ENTER+to go on to the next tutorial panel
)INIT
  &EPF = PFK(END)
  IF (&EPF = &Z)
    &EPF = 'END'
  &D = TRUNC(&EPF,2)
  &DT = .TRAIL
  &D = TRUNC(&DT,1)
  IF (&D = '0')
    &DT = .TRAIL
    &EPF = 'PF&DT'
)PROC
)END
